{
  "text": "where f N is a measure of fractional native population, T is the full width at half maximum of |df N /dT | and T F is the folding transition temperature identified with the maximum in [CITATION_1] may then be defined by the heat capacity related quantities in equation [CITATION_2] . Using this expression, c is computed to be \u22481620, 1750 and 2030, respectively, for db = /10, /5 and 5 /9. Thus, when measured in terms of transition sharpness, the thermodynamic cooperativity of these calorimetrically two-state models do increase with elementary pairwise desolvation barrier height.",
